findings.lower_chest: Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. There is no evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion.
findings.hepatobiliary: A couple of scattered tiny hypodensities in the liver, possibly hepatic cysts or biliary hamartomas. Otherwise, the liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation throughout. No evidence of focal lesions or biliary dilatation.
findings.pancreas: Normal attenuation throughout, without evidence of focal lesions or pancreatic ductal dilatation.
findings.spleen: Normal size and attenuation throughout, without evidence of focal lesions.
findings.urinary: Normal and symmetric kidneys with normal nephrogram. A couple tiny subcentimeter hypodensities in bilateral kidneys.
findings.gastrointestinal: Focal bowel wall thickening with surrounding inflammatory fat stranding along a segment of diverticula containing transverse colon. A few small locules of extraluminal air are seen. No abnormal fluid collection concerning for abscess.
findings.pelvis: Unremarkable urinary bladder and distal ureters. No free fluid in the pelvis.
findings.vascular: No abdominal aortic aneurysm. Mild atherosclerotic disease noted.
findings.bones: No evidence of acute fracture. Multiple Schmorl's nodes along lower thoracic vertebrae. Probable hemangioma in L3 vertebrae.
findings.soft_tissues: Abdominal and pelvic wall within normal limits.
